cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the incorporation of Artificial Intelligence in decision-making procedures and the need for explainable decision procedures. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper also discusses the importance of these decision procedures being explainable to the people involved in them, which suggests a focus on Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also reviews existing approaches to explanation in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and discusses the desiderata for truly explainable decision systems, which could fall under the sub-categories of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
